4. One‑Page Text Companion (“System Architecture – Notes”)
Add a short text page:

Oasis is a multi‑tier, cloud‑hosted web application with a browser‑based client, stateless backend services, and managed data stores.

Authentication uses SSO/MFA (where configured) and centralized auth/session service; authorization is enforced via role‑based access in backend services.

Customer data (accounts, workspace metadata, stored content) is stored in managed databases and object storage in private networks, encrypted at rest and accessed only via backend services.

Logging, monitoring, CI/CD, and secrets management support secure operations and are restricted to authorized engineering/DevOps staff.